{"type":"text","timestamp":1775853517728,"sessionID":"ses_286e29dccffelYrnwbzojSioQ7","part":{"id":"prt_d791e26b90015crMzUrDhk4Ki1","messageID":"msg_d791dfdca0012eImTgvANhxI4j","sessionID":"ses_286e29dccffelYrnwbzojSioQ7","type":"text","text":"Based on my analysis of the codebase and logs, here's the archive summary for AR-012:\n\n## AR-012 — 会话存储接口定义 (Session Storage Interface Definition)\n\n**What was completed:**\n\n1. **Core interface** - Full `Store` interface implementation with all required methods (Ping, GetSandboxBySessionID, StoreSandbox, UpdateSandbox, DeleteSandboxBySessionID, ListExpiredSandboxes, ListInactiveSandboxes, UpdateSessionLastActivity, Close)\n\n2. **Redis backend** - Complete `redisStore` implementation with:\n   - Session storage using `session:{id}` keys\n   - Expiry and activity ZSET indexes for garbage collection\n   - Pipeline operations for atomicity\n   - Proper error handling including `ErrNotFound`\n\n3. **Valkey backend** - Complete `valkeyStore` implementation with:\n   - Builder-style API usage\n   - Same key structure and indexing as Redis\n   - Proper nil/error handling with `IsValkeyNil`\n\n4. **Singleton pattern** - Thread-safe `Storage()` function using `sync.Once`\n\n5. **Configuration** - Environment variable support for both backends:\n   - `REDIS_ADDR`, `REDIS_PASSWORD`, `STORE_TYPE` for Redis\n   - `VALKEY_ADDR`, `VALKEY_PASSWORD`, `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE`, `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` for Valkey\n\n6. **Testing** - Comprehensive unit tests using `miniredis`:\n   - All interface methods covered\n   - Error paths tested\n   - Edge cases (nil, empty IDs, zero times)\n\n7. **Documentation** - Design document with architecture details, API contracts, and deployment considerations\n\n**What was deferred:**\n\n1. **Integration tests** - Tests with real Redis/Valkey instances (only miniredis used)\n\n2. **Performance testing** - No benchmark tests or load testing\n\n3. **Monitoring metrics** - No Prometheus/metrics instrumentation\n\n4. **Advanced features** - Retry mechanisms for transient failures, compression for large documents, local caching layer\n\n5. **Cluster optimizations** - Hash tags for Redis cluster slot consistency notes in design but not enforced in code","time":{"start":1775853517726,"end":1775853517726}}}
